Embarking on your UPSC journey? Need personal guidance and support?

Many overlook the true essence of preparing for this esteemed exam. While the ideal booklist is common knowledge, few manage to retain and study the subjects in an integrated manner. Academic resources are readily available, but clearing UPSC demands much more than just studying.

I'm Prachi Verma, a dedicated personal academic mentor. If you're interested in knowing more about my qualifications, visit my page. Unlike typical academic mentors who hand over a to-do list and leave students to fend for themselves, my approach is different. I offer a personalized experience with one-on-one sessions, helping students from various academic fields rebuild their focus through empirical research strategies and a unique blend of philosophy.

Your personal and professional life will be heard, and you'll be given the space to explore your options. My sessions also include discussions with students who are building backup options and balancing other academic or professional activities alongside UPSC preparation.

Take the first step towards supporting your mental health and academic progression for market readiness. Experience the difference yourself by enrolling for the 1:1 sessions .

Below is my Topmate account, click on the website to know more about the session. An usual session is 40 mins long that costs INR300 rupees while people who have very specific short questions pre decided, can book the option for a 15-20 min 1:1 call that costs INR 125. 
For further details, you can DM me your doubts and I'll be ready to help. My experience involves working with Catalyst Learning Services based in Kolkata as a junior academic guide.
